body:
This issue is addressed by providing a set of concrete implemenations of IPipelineDataConverter for arrays of type:
	float[];
	double[];
	int[]; and
	long[].

Unit tests have been written for these, and abstracted in a way to cover additional array-types with minimal effort.

Summary of changes:
   * Create Driver and Client configuration modules for the Unmanaged AM app, and add extra parameters required for that mode;
   * Implement Unmanaged AM app submission functionality;
   * Make `YarnDriverConfigurationProviderImpl` class public so that Unmanaged AM configuration can refer to it.

JIRA: [REEF-1686](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-1686)

Closes #

   * Make code more readable and idiomatic;
   * Log all running threads at the end of the **client** process;
   * remove references to `BindException` from the example and from `DriverLauncher`;

**NOTE:** The updated HelloREEF example can be used to verify that all threads are closed before the client exit as per [REEF-1721](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-1721) (PR #1234).

JIRA: [REEF-1724](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/REEF-1724)
